by seriquynh at 2024-06-28T08:30:13Z

I first though CompletionInput::__toString() should have string as return type because ArgvInput::__toString() already had string as return type (ComplentionInput extends ArgvInput). If a class doesn't extend anything, __toString() without type-hint is fine.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by nicolas-grekas at 2024-06-28T08:40:04Z

The `string` return type is implicit on `__toString()` methods so technically it's not needed, but better be explicit.
